The paper discusses a new bibliographic database and its coverage and features, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it directly relates to the topic of the paper. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as the paper discusses the search and retrieval of scientific information. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the impact of a new database on the scientific community. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper discusses the citation analysis and coverage of scientific literature.
